Business Brief -- Yorkville Federal Savings  Loan:
   Ex-Developer Pleads Guilty
   To Bribing Thrift Officers
Mr. Alexander also pleaded guilty to making false
statements on loan documents to get $1.5 million in personal
loans from Yorkville in 1986 and 1987. The two thrift
officers haven't been charged, according to prosecutors.
   Yorkville was declared insolvent and put into receivership
in September 1990.
   Mr. Alexander was releasd on $250,000 bond. He'll be
sentenced July 21.